; box, tech. activated by techy. improves mechs quickness 10 percent
INUMBER 1087
NAME 363
*DESCRIPTION_START
You see a small, black box made of a smooth, cool material.
*DESCRIPTION_END
TECH
SUBSTANCE BRITTLE
VOLUME 1
WEIGHT 1
ARTICLE THE
VARIABLE MECHQUITEMP
IFPREVERB PUSH -1
  IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 0
      IFVAR INTNUM68 > 19 ; If technologist is better than Technician
        CLEARVERB
        EQUAL ITEMVAL5 1
        ECHO PLAYER Using your technological understanding, you place the device in ready mode.
        ECHO OTHERS %n touches %a.
        ECHO ALL %cA low hum is emitted.
      ELSE
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You touch various surfaces of %a, but nothing seems to happen.
        ECHO OTHERS %n touches %a, but nothing seems to happen..
      ENDIF
  ELSE
    IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 1
      IFVAR RAC = 7
        IFVAR INTNUM53 = 0
          IFVAR QUI < 130
            CLEARVERB
            EQUAL ITEMVAL5 0
            EQUAL INTNUM53 1
            ECHO PLAYER You place %a against your chest-housing and feel a suffed surge of power that lasts a breif moment.
            ECHO OTHERS %n places %a against %h chest-housing and involuntarily stiffens for a moment.
			ECHO ALL %cThe low hum suddenly stops.
            EQUAL MECHQUITEMP QUI
            DIV MECHQUITEMP 10
            ADD QUIT MECHQUITEMP
            EQUAL QUI QUIT
            GMMSG ** %n's quickness inreased by ten-percent.
          ELSE
            CLEARVERB
            ECHO PLAYER You place %a against your chest-housing, but nothing happens.
            ECHO OTHERS %n places %a against %h chest-housing, but nothing happens.
            ECHO ALL %cThe low hum suddenly stops.
            EQUAL ITEMVAL5 0
          ENDIF
        ELSE
          CLEARVERB
          ECHO PLAYER You place %a against your chest-housing, but nothing happens.
          ECHO OTHERS %n places %a against %h chest-housing, but nothing happens.
          ECHO ALL %cThe low hum suddenly stops.
          EQUAL ITEMVAL5 0
        ENDIF
      ELSE
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You play around with %a, unsure of what to do with it.
        ECHO OTHERS %n looks pretty funny as %s plays around with %a.
        EQUAL ITEMVAL5 0
        ECHO ALL %cSuddenly, the low hum stops.
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF

