;  Auction items - June 26, 1994.


; Crystal life form
INUMBER 1069
NAME 978
WEIGHT 5
VOLUME 5
ARMOR
SUBSTANCE BRITTLE
*DESCRIPTION_START
It appears to be a rather large, uncut gem of some sort. Crystaline in
shape and formation, it is nearly transparent and glows oddly when the
light shines through it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB LOOK -1
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER %c **  AUCTION ITEM. June 26, 1994. KREEBONKER  **%c
    ECHO PLAYER %c **  A rock brought back from the Tot
    ECHO PLAYER        star system, many people have argued if this
    ECHO PLAYER        piece of crystal is sentient. All attempts at
    ECHO PLAYER        this point to communicate with it have failed. **
  ELSE
   RANDOM DUMMY1 1 10 0
   IFVAR DUMMY1 = 1
    ECHO OTHERS %cYou see a luminous glow coming from %n.
    ECHO PLAYER You see a luminous glow eminating from inside the lattice of the crystal.
    spell 209 100
   ENDIF
   IFVAR DUMMY1 = 2
     ECHO PLAYER %cYou can hear a beautiful resonance as the light plays through the crystal.
     ECHO OTHERS All around you, a beautiful resonance fills the air.
     spell 102 100
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 3
    ECHO ALL %cSomething touches your mind, gently.
    spell 225 100
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 4
    ECHO PLAYER %cSuddenly, the crystal glows white hot, forcing you to look away!
    ECHO OTHERS Suddenly, an incredibly bright light eminates from %n forcing you to look away!
    spell 317 100
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFVERB TOUCH -1
  ECHO PLAYER %cAs you touch the crystal, you feel something touch your mind for an instant, and then vanish.
ENDIF


; chip for mechanoids
;
; ITEMBIT2: 1 increases Strength by ITEMVAL5 permanently.
; ITEMBIT3: 1 increases Perception by ITEMVAL5 permanently.
; ITEMBIT4: 1 increases Quickness by ITEMVAL5 permanently.
; ITEMBIT5: 1 increases Willpower by ITEMVAL5 permanently.
; ITEMBIT6: 1 increases Consitution by ITEMVAL5 permanently.
; ITEMBIT7: 1 increases Agility by ITEMVAL5 permanently.
; ITEMBIT8: 1 increases Empathy by ITEMVAL5 permanentyly.
INUMBER 1986
NAME 1590
TECH
SUBSTANCE BRITTLE
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 1
*DESCRIPTION_START
A tiny piece of plastic and metal, no bigger than your fingertip.
Six small metal prongs stick out on either side.
*DESCRIPTION_END

variable skotempvalue1
variable skotempvalue2
variable skotempvalue3


IFPREVERB WEAR -1
   IFVAR RAC = 7
     IFVAR ITEMBIT2 = 1
       equal skotempvalue1 str
       add skotempvalue1 itemval5
       ifvar skotempvalue1 > 135
       	equal skotempvalue1 135
       endif
       EQUAL STR skotempvalue1
       EQUAL STRT skotempvalue1
       STRCVT 0 str
       GMMSG ** %n's strength set to %0 by a chip.
       EQUAL ROUNDTIME 30
       REMOVEITEM -1
       CLEARVERB
       ECHO PLAYER You flip open the panel to your main proccessor.
       ECHO OTHERS You see %n flip open a panel on %h head.
       PLREVENT 2
       CONTPLREVENT
       ECHO PLAYER %cYou carefully install the chip in a free slot.
       ECHO OTHERS %cYou see %n place the chip into a slot and push it down firmly.
       PLREVENT 2
       CONTPLREVENT
       ECHO PLAYER %cYou close up the panel again.
       ECHO OTHERS %cYou see %n close up the panel again.
       ECHO PLAYER %cYou re-route power throught the chip.
       ECHO PLAYER %cStrength functions adjusted.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR ITEMBIT3 = 1
       equal skotempvalue1 per
       add skotempvalue1 itemval5
       ifvar skotempvalue1 > 135
       	equal skotempvalue1 135
       endif
       EQUAL per skotempvalue1
       EQUAL pert skotempvalue1
       STRCVT 0 per
       GMMSG ** %n's perception set to %0 by a chip.
       EQUAL ROUNDTIME 30
       REMOVEITEM -1
       CLEARVERB
       ECHO PLAYER You flip open the panel to your main proccessor.
       ECHO OTHERS You see %n flip open a panel on %h head.
       PLREVENT 2
       CONTPLREVENT
       ECHO PLAYER %cYou carefully install the chip in a free slot.
       ECHO OTHERS %cYou see %n place the chip into a slot and push it down firmly.
       PLREVENT 2
       CONTPLREVENT
       ECHO PLAYER %cYou close up the panel again.
       ECHO OTHERS %cYou see %n close up the panel again.
       ECHO PLAYER %cYou re-route power throught the chip.
       ECHO PLAYER %Perception functions adjusted.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR ITEMBIT4 = 1
       equal skotempvalue1 QUI
       add skotempvalue1 itemval5
       ifvar skotempvalue1 > 135
       	equal skotempvalue1 135
       endif
